Knit a Report

R Markdown and Knitr

This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document.

Our Report

Orange Countys unemployment rate drops off a cliff in 2010, yet still has some bumps in the line during that decade.

Heres our quick spot check of the dataset, counting months present in the data for each year for Orange County.

With a click of Knit in RStudio, heres a report in an easily shareable HTML format, indicating that the data is missing some rows for Orange County.

RMarkdown can be knit into many, many common formats including Word, PDF, HTML, and slides. Other packages extend on this allowing for books, letters, blogs, and posters to be knit from RMarkdown.
